{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τόλμ-ᾰ</b>, ης, ἡ, <br /> also <b>τόλμη</b>, which [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista “Praeparatio Sophistica” p.114 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus compares with πρύμνη for πρύμνα\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: but (apart from πρὸς τόλμην πεσεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 11 (Papyrus), which is not guaranteed by the metre) only the form τόλμᾰ (_accusative_ τόλμᾰν, e. g. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 862)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] occurs in <i>Attic dialect</i> and Trag., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 702, “Ion” 1264, “fragment” 426 (in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1416, ἥ γε τόλμα σου (conjecture Jodrell) is the probable reading), 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.82, 6.59, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 193d, “R.” 575a, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 15.144, “POxy.” 1119.8 (3rd c.AD), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so in <i>Ionic dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.135 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but τόλμη (<i>nominative</i>) in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Clitarchus Gnomologus 35J., _accusative_ τόλμην LXX.Jdt.16.10(12) codex 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]: <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>τόλμᾱ</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 9.82, 13.11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>courage, hardihood,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus [same places], 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.121.ζ, Trag. and _Attic dialect_ (see. above)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τόλμα καλῶν <b>courage for</b> noble acts, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 7.59 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῶνδε τόλμαν σχεθεῖν to have <b>courage</b> or <b>nerve</b> for this business, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 16. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in bad sense, <b>over-boldness, recklessness,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ch.” 1004 (996); πῶς οὖν.. ἐς τόδ᾽ ἂν τόλμης ἔβ; 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 125, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1264, etc.; τόλμης ἔργα κἀναισχυντίας 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 702; τ. ἀλόγιστος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.82, compare 6.59; τ. καὶ ἀναίδεια 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 3.3.5, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 6.46; θρασύτης καὶ τ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 197b; τ. καὶ ἀναισχυντία [prev. author] “Ap.” 38d; ἡ ἄφρων τ. [prev. author] “La.” 193d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>a bold</b> or <b>daring act,</b> φίλτρα τόλμης τῆσδε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 1029 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τόλμας (<i>genitive</i>), ἃν ἔρεξα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 838 (Lyric poetry): _plural_, κακὰς δὲ τόλμας μήτ᾽ ἐπισταίμην ἐγώ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 582, compare “Aj.” 46; ἀνόσιοι πληγῶν τ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 881a, compare “Ep.” 336d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Pythagoras Philosophus name for 2, Anatol. cited in “Theologumena Arithmeticae” 8. (see. Τλάω.) \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9458","accentedUnicode":"τόλμα","shortDef":"daring","mediumDef":"daring","stepGloss":"daring","stepTransliteration":"tolma","_step_Type":"word"}]}